title: Unwavering Mark
note: You menace your foes, foiling their attacks and punishing them for harming others.
description: While mounted and on hit, mark the target with disadvantage on attack rolls that don't target you for one turn. If the marked target doesn't attack you, make a special melee weapon attack with advantage (weapon attack damage + half your fighter level) against it as a bonus action. You can mark multiple enemies up to your Strength modifier per session.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Warding Maneuver
note: You learn to fend off strikes directed at you, your mount, or other creatures nearby.
description: While wielding a melee weapon or sheild and if an attacking creature hits an ally within 5 feet of you, roll 1d8 as a reaction and add the value + resistance to your ally's AC. This ability can be used a max of your Constitution modifier per session.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Hold The Line
note: From atop a mount, your enemies are feebly below you.
description: While mounted, creatures within 10 feet provoke an opportunity attack from you when they move within your reach, and when hit, speed is reduced to 0 until the end of the current turn.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Ferocious Charger
note: The skill of a mounted fighter runs through your blood so run down your foes, whether you're mounted or not.
description: When you move 10 feet in a straight line right before attacking a creature you hit, that target must succeed on a Strength saving throw (DC 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Strength modifier) or be knocked prone. You can use this feature only once on each of your turns.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Vigilant Defender
note: You respond to danger with extraordinary vigilance.
description: While in combat, gain a special reaction to make an opportunity attack that you take once on every creature's turn, except your own.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Fighting Spirit
note: Intensity in battle is a shield and guides the blade strike true.
description: As a bonus action, gain advantage on all weapon attack rolls until the end of your turn. Gain 5 temporary hit points. You can use this feature three times per session.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Samurai's Bonus Proficiency
note: Sensei has taught you the way of their homeland.
description: Learn a new language and gain proficiency in one skill: History, Insight, Performance, or Persuasion.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Elegant Courtier
note: Discipline and attention to detail allow you to excel in social situations.
description: Charisma (Persuasion) checks = 1d20 + Charisma + Wisdom modifier. You also gain proficiency in Wisdom, Intelligence, or Charisma saving throws.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Fighting Spirit 1+
note: Battle heat grants your strikes to hone in on your enemies.
description: As a bonus action, gain advantage on all weapon attack rolls until the end of your turn. Gain 10 temporary hit points. You can use this feature three times per session.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Tireless Spirit
note: Your training and experience keeps the fight alive in you.
description: You regain one use of Fighting Spirit at the begining of an encounter.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Fighting Spirit 2+
note: The battle ground is where your blade thrives.
description: As a bonus action, gain advantage on all weapon attack rolls until the end of your turn. Gain 15 temporary hit points. You can use this feature three times per session.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Rapid Strike
note: You learn to trade accuracy for swift strikes.
description: On an attack action that has advantage, you can trade the advantage roll for an additional weapon attack against that target.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Strength Before Death
note: A fighting spirit can delay the grasp of death.
description: At 0 health points, use your reaction to immediately take an extra turn, but taking damage causes death saving throw failures as normal. When the extra turn ends, you fall unconscious if you still have 0 hit points. One use per session.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Manifest Echo
note: Magically manifest an echo of yourself in an unoccupied space. This echo is a magical, translucent, and gray image of you.
description: Use a bonus action to manifest an echo of yourself in a space you can see within 15 feet. The echo has AC 14 + your proficiency bonus, 1 hit point, move 30 feet, immunity to all conditions, saving throw bonus rolls, same size as you, and occupies space. You mentally command this echo. You can magically swap places with your echo as a bonus action. Your echo has opportunity attacks for creatures within 5 feet. When you attack, you can originate your attack from your echo. This echo lasts until it is destroyed, dismissed as a bonus action, manifest another echo, further than 30 feet away, or you are incapacitated.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Unleash Incarnation
note: You can heighten your echo's fury.
description: When you Attack, make one additional melee attack from the echo's position. You can use this feature a max of your Constitution modifier per session.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Echo Avatar
note: Your connection to your echo is now a portal for your consciousness to transfer to your echo.
description: As an action, see and hear through your echo whilst you stay deafened and blinded for up to 10 minutes. Your echo can move up to 1,000 feet away from you without being destroyed during this ability.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Shadow Martyr
note: Throw your echo in front of an attack directed at another creature that you can see.
description: Use your reaction to teleport the echo to an unoccupied space within 5 feet of the targeted creature. The attack roll is now made against your echo. You can use ability once per session.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Reclaim Potential
note: Absorb the fleeting magic of your echo.
description: When your echo is destroyed by taking damage, you gain temporary hit points equal to 2d6 + your Constitution modifier. You can use this ability a max of your Constitution modifier per session.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Legion Of One
note: You are a walking legion of knights.
description: Use a bonus action to create two echos with Manifest Echo. Additionally at the start of combat, you regain one use of Unleash Incarnation.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Psionic Power
note: Harbor a wellspring of psionic energy from within.
description: You gain a new play die; a Psionic Energy dice to the amount of twice your proficiency bonus d6. These fuel various psionic powers by expending them and are regained per session. At the start of any battle you regain one Psionic Energy die as a bonus action.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Psionic Protective Field
note: Create a momentary shield of telekinetic force.
description: Use your reaction to expend and roll one Psionic Energy die, and reduce the damage taken by a creature you see within 30 feet by the roll plus your Intelligence modifier.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Psionic Strike
note: Propel your weapons with psionic force.
description: After you attack, hit, and damage a target, expend and roll one Psionic Energy die to deal additional force damage equal to roll plus your Intelligence modifier.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Telekinetic Movement
note: Move an object or a creature with your mind.
description: As an action, target one visible loose object or willing creature within 30 feet, other than yourself, and move it up to 30 feet once per session.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Psionic Power 1+
note: The spring of psionic energy grows into a fountain.
description: The size of your Psionic Energy dice increases to d8.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Psi-Powered Leap
note: You have mastered new ways to use your telekinetic abilities and propel your body with your mind.
description: As a bonus action, you gain a flying speed equal to twice your walking speed until end of turn, once per session unless you expend a Psionic Energy die to regain it next turn.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Telekinetic Thrust
note: You have mastered new ways to use your telekinetic abilities to knock down your target.
description: After you deal damage with Psionic Strike, the target must succeed a Strength saving throw DC 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Intelligence modifier, or else be knocked prone or moved up to 10 feet horizontally.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Guarded Mind
note: The psionic energy flowing through you has bolstered your mind.
description: Gain resistance to psychic damage. Additionally expend a Psionic Energy die to cleanse Charmed or Frightened conditions off yourself.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Psionic Power 2+
note: Psionic energy is your to flourish into a waterfall.
description: The size of your Psionic Energy dice increases to d10.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Bulwark Of Force
note: Shield yourself and others with telekinetic force.
description: As a bonus action, choose a number up to your Intelligence modifier of creatures, including yourself, that you see within 30 feet, to be protected by half cover for one combat round. You can do this once per session unless you expend a Psionic Energy die to regain it next turn.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Psionic Power 3+
note: The ocean of Psionic energy inside you now yours to do your bidding.
description: The size of your Psionic Energy dice increases to d12.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Telekinetic Master
note: Your ability to move creatures and objects with your mind is matched by few.
description: Cast Telekinesis, requiring no components, spellcasting ability using Intelligence, and hold a concentration spell. You now make one attack with a weapon as a bonus action. You can do this once per session, unless you expend a Psionic Energy die to regain it next turn.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Eldrich Spellcasting
note: Augment your martial prowess with the ability to cast spells. Abjuration spells grant additional protection in battle, while evocation spells deal damage to many foes at once.
description:
Obtain (2) two cantrips and (2) two 1st level spells of your choice from the wizard spell list. Selected spells must be from abjuration or evocation, will utilize your Intelligence ability, and are committed to memory.  To cast a spell, expend a spell slot, from a total of (2) two 1st level spells slots, of equal level or higher. You regain all level spell slots at the beginning of each session.
Spell save DC = 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Intelligence modifier
Spell attack modifier = your proficiency bonus + your Intelligence modifier
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Weapon Bond
note: Soulbind youself through ritual and create a magical bond between yourself and up to two weapon.
description: Perform the 1 hour ritual, touching the chosen weapon, and forge the bond. You can no longer be disarmed of that weapon. Magically teleport summon that weapon to your hand as a bonus action. You can have up to two bonded weapons.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Eldrich Spellcasting 1+
note: Augment your martial prowess with the ability to cast spells.
description: Obtain an additional 1st level spell slot for a total of (2) two cantrips and (3) three 1st level spells slots.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Eldrich Spellcasting 2+
note: Augment your martial prowess with the ability to cast spells. New spells selected can be from any school of magic.
description: Obtain an additional 1st level and two 2nd level spell slots, for a total of (2) two cantrips, (4) four 1st level, and (2) two 2nd level spell slots.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: War Magic
note: Prioritize your magic abilities before you stike with your blade.
description: Use your attack action to cast a cantrip and then make one weapon attack as a bonus action.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Eldritch Strike
note: Weapon strikes undercut a creature's resistance to your spells.
description: On hit with a weapon attack, that target has disadvantage on the next saving throw it makes against a spell you cast.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Eldrich Spellcasting 3+
note: Augment your martial prowess with the ability to cast spells.
description: Obtain an additional cantrip and 2nd level spell slot, for a total of (3) three cantrips, (4) four 1st level, and (3) three 2nd level spell slots.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Eldrich Spellcasting 4+
note: Augment your martial prowess with the ability to cast spells. New spells selected can be from any school of magic.
description: Obtain two 3rd level spell slots, for a total of (3) three cantrips, (4) four 1st level, (3) three 2nd level, and (2) two 3rd level spell slots.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Arcane Charge
note: A fighter's Action Surge opens an arcane opporunity to teleport.
description: Teleport up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space you can see when you use your Action Surge. You can teleport before or after the additional action.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Eldrich Spellcasting 5+
note: Augment your martial prowess with the ability to cast spells.
description: Obtain an additional 3rd level spell slot, for a total of (3) three cantrips, (4) four 1st level, (3) three 2nd level, and (3) three 3rd level spell slots.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Improved War Magic
note: Prioritize your magic spells before you stike with your blade.
description: Use your action to cast a spell and then make one weapon attack as a bonus action.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Eldrich Spellcasting 6+
note: Augment your martial prowess with the ability to cast spells. New spells selected can be from any school of magic.
description: Obtain a 4th level spell slot, for a total of (3) three cantrips, (4) four 1st level, (3) three 2nd level, (3) three 3rd level, and (1) one 4th level spell slots.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: A Giants' Proficiency
description: Gain proficiency with smith’s tools, and you learn to speak, read, and write Giant.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Cloud Rune
note: This rune emulates the deceptive magic used by some cloud giants.
description: Inscribe this rune and while equipped, gain advantage on Sleight of Hand and Deception checks. Additionally, once per session, you redirect someone else's damage attack that you can see within 30 feet to another target within same range.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Fire Rune
note: This rune's magic channels the masterful craftsmanship of great smiths. Your target will be restrained by flame shackles that burn it alive.
description: Inscribe this rune and while equipped, gain double tool proficiency bonus ability check. Additionally, once per session, on a hit attack, attack damage add 2d6 fire damage, and target must succeed a Strength saving throw DC 8 + proficiency bonus + Constitution modifer or be restrained and takes 2d6 fire damage at the start of each of its turns until succeeds on the saving throw each turn.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Frost Rune
note: This rune's magic evokes the might of those who survive in the wintry wilderness, such as frost giants. Invoking the rune increase your sturdiness.
description: Inscribe this rune and while equipped, gain advantage on Animal Handling and Intimidation checks. Additionally, once per session, as a bonus action, you gain a +2 bonus to all Strength and Constitution ability checks and saving throws.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Giant Might
note: Imbue yourself with the might of giants and magically gain the benefits.
description: As a bonus action and for one minute, grow Large, including attire, if the space allows, then gain advantage on Strength checks and saving throws. One of your attacks deals an additional 1d6 damage to a target on a hit. Max ability uses up to proficiency bonus per session.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Rune Carver
note: Capture the discovered Giant's Runes, their language of text, and find the power they use on your gear.
description: Choose (2) two runes to add to your Runes Known table. Once per session, inscribe one of each rune onto a weapon, armor, shield, jewelry, or equippable item for it to remain for the entire session. Rune Magic saving throw DC 8 + proficiency bonus + Constitution modifer.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Stone Rune
note: This rune's magic channels the judiciousness associated with stone giants. The charm of grounding someone into a dreamy stupor.
description: Inscribe this rune and while equipped, gain advantage on Insight checks and gain 120 feet darkvision. Additionally, once per session, as a reaction, if a creature within 30 feet ends its turn, must succeed a Wisdom saving throw else be charmed with zero speed and incapacitation, rerolling each turn.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Hill Rune
note: This rune's magic bestows a resilience reminiscent of a hill giant.
description: Inscribe this rune and while equipped, gain resistance to Poison and advantage on Poison saving throws. Additionally, once per session, as bonus action, gain resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Rune Carver 1+
note: Understanding the Giant's Runes provides opportunity to channel their ancient power.
description: Gain an additional rune slot for a total of (3) three runes in your Runes Known table. Once per session, inscribe one of each rune onto a weapon, armor, shield, jewelry, or equippable item for it to remain for the entire session.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Storm Rune
note: Use this rune to enter a prophetic state and gain a glimpse into the future like a storm seer giant.
description: Inscribe this rune and while equipped, gain advantage on Arcana and immunity to Surprise. Additionally, once per session, as a bonus action, when you or a creature within 60 feet make any roll, it can be rerolled with advantage or disadvantage.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Great Stature
note: The magic of your runes permanently alters you.
description: Roll 3d4 and permanently grow that number of inches in height. The extra damage you deal with your Giant's Might ability increases to 1d8.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Rune Carver 2+
note: You use the power of the Giant's Runes to better connect to their magic and mysticism.
description: Gain an additional rune slot for a total of (4) four runes in your Runes Known table. Once per session, inscribe one of each rune onto a weapon, armor, shield, jewelry, or equippable item for it to remain for the entire session.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Runic Shield
note: Invoke this rune's magic to protect your allies.
description: When a creature within 60 feet is hit by an attack roll, use your reaction to force the attacker to reroll  the hit die d20. You can ability up to your proficiency bonus per session.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Master of Runes
note: Expand the power of Giants throughout your being increasing the mystic capacities you hold.
description: You can invoke each rune twice from your Rune Carver ability and Runes Known table, and regain all expended uses at the start of each session.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Rune Carver 3+
note: You inherit the abilities of the ancient Giants. They're mystic ways are natural to you as a language and a way of life.
description: Gain an additional rune slot for a total of (5) five runes in your Runes Known table. Once per session, inscribe one of each rune onto a weapon, armor, shield, jewelry, or equippable item for it to remain for the entire session.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast

title: Runic Juggernaut
note: Amplify the Giants' rune-powered transformation. You are a Giant.
description: Giant's Might's extra damage increases to 1d10, increase size to Huge, and reach increases by 5 feet.
signature: Abridged from Player's Handbook by Wizards of the Coast
